    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — FEA compression-bending QoI response to material and geometric inputs",
    "description": "A Sobol-index global sensitivity analysis (N=4096 quasi-random LHS samples) was performed varying cortical bone modulus (±20%), cancellous bone modulus (±40%), titanium alloy yield strength (±5%), screw outer diameter (±0.15 mm), and fixation block polyaxial constraint stiffness (±30%). Construct stiffness exhibited dominant first-order sensitivity to cortical bone modulus (S1=0.42) and screw diameter (S1=0.31); yield force was most sensitive to titanium yield strength (S1=0.57). Total-order indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions, supporting the decision to treat material properties as the primary uncertainty drivers in the UQ propagation.",
    "method": "Sobol variance-decomposition (Saltelli 2010 estimator)",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "cortical bone modulus",
      "screw outer diameter",
      "titanium alloy yield strength"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 4096
  },
