      "name": "Non-cannulated pedicle screw applicability domain",
      "description": "The credibility assessment applies exclusively to solid (non-cannulated) titanium-alloy pedicle screws with nominal outer diameter 7.0–8.0 mm and thread pitch 2.75–3.0 mm, tested in UHMWPE fixation blocks per ASTM F1717-21. The model is not applicable to cannulated screws, fenestrated screws, PEEK-bodied screws, or dynamic stabilisation constructs. Patient-specific bone geometry is explicitly out of scope; the polyaxial head constraint is modelled as a rigid coupling and is not valid for multi-axial fatigue scenarios."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
